The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses,
and share prices are as of market close in  Lima .  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  rose 0.5 percent to 20,744.49. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index slid 0.2 percent to 2,656.48.  Panoro Minerals Ltd. (PML)  , a Canadian copper and gold
exploration company, jumped 14 percent to 67 cents as copper
advanced for a second day in New York and investors bet the
company will take on partner to develop its properties, said
Jose Luis Bustamante, head of trading at Cartisa SAB.  Rio Alto Mining Ltd. (RIO)  , a Canadian gold miner, rose
3.1 percent to $4.04 after gold gained in New York.  Cia. de Minas Buenaventura SAA  (BVN PE), the countryâ€™s
biggest precious-metals miner, climbed 2.1 percent to $38.95.  Maple Energy Plc (MPLE)  , the oil and natural gas
producer with operations in Peru, advanced 1 percent to $1.04
after crude gained in  New York .  To contact the reporter on this story:
